definition: to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
to raise (animals)/to bring up (children)/to keep (pets)/to support/to give birth

sentences.english: My mother gave birth to eleven children, but only seven survived.
sentences.chinese: 我的母亲生养了十一个孩子，就留下了我们七个。

sentences.english: Rich in eyebrow have energy, yellow brown hue, youth and sweet.
sentences.chinese: 富含眉毛生养能量，黄褐色调，青春甜美，活泼俏丽。

sentences.english: Rich in eyebrow have energy, soft black hue. Crystal of intelligence.
sentences.chinese: 富含睫毛生养能量，柔黑色调，明澈智能。

sentences.english: That's what having children felt like for me.
sentences.chinese: 这对于我来说就像生养孩子的感觉似的。

sentences.english: Female have one calf ?one metre long at birth, after 12 month gestation period.
sentences.chinese: 母海豚经过12个月的孕育期生养一头小海豚。

sentences.english: And you， be ye fruitful， and multiply； bring forth abundantly in the earth， and multiply therein.
sentences.chinese: 你们要生养众多，在地上昌盛繁茂。

sentences.english: Therefore Michal the daughter of Saul had no child unto the day of her death.
sentences.chinese: 扫罗的女儿米甲，直到死日，没有生养儿女。

sentences.english: And Salah lived after he begat Eber four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.
sentences.chinese: 之后又活了四百三十年，生养了其他的儿女。

to become pregnant/to carry a child in the womb
